MAJ. THOMAS RANDOLPH,
GENT., 363 acs. (N. L.), Henrico Co;
on N. side of the Flue Anna (Riv.);
adj. land of Mr. Thomas Crooke, dec’d;
9 July 1724, p. 3. 40 Shill,

ROBERT ALLIN, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Hanover Co; on N. side of Chicohominy Sw; beg. adj. Capt. Thompson;
9 July 1724, p. 31. 40 Shill.

JOHN HOLLODAY, 400 acs. (N.
L.), King Wm. Co., in St. John’s Par;
on N. side the North Anna (Riv.); on
head brs. of Beverdam Cr; beg. at
Robert Axton, in Mathew Creed’s line;
on S, side the Road to Toppin Castle;
on James Harrison’s line; 9 July 1724,
p. 94, 40 Shill,

JOSHUA IRBY, 400 acs, (N. L.),
on upper side of Waquiyough Creek;
9 July 1724, p. 61. 40 Shill.

THOMAS BOTTOM, of Henrico
Co., 300 acs, (N. L.), Pr. Geo. Co;
in the fork of Knib’s & Flatt Creeks;
9 July 1724, p, 65. 30 Shill.

JOSHUA PRITCHET, 199 acs. (N.
L.), Pr. Geo. Co; on S. side of Butterwood Sw; below mouth of Jupiter’s Br;
9 July 1724, p. 74. 20 Shill.

RICHARD BLOW, 300 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; S. side of the main Blackwater Sw; on S. side of Seacock Sw;
adj. his own; & land of Edmund Bartow; 9 July 1724, p. 90. 30 Shill.

CAPT. THOMAS CARR, JUNR.,
400 acs, (N. L.), King Wm. Co., in
St. Margaret’s Par; on both sides of
Polecat (Sw.); adj. Robert Chandler;
Mr. William Terrel; & Richard Rookes;
22 Feb. 1724, p. 148. 40 Shill.

THOMAS HOUSE, JUNR., 350 acs.
(N. L.), Surry Co; on N. side of the
Three Creeks; adj. George Pasmore;
Henry Baites; & Nicholas Hatch’s line;
22 Feb. 1724, p. 171. 35 Shill.

WILLIAM REEVES, of Pr. Geo, Co;
200 acs. (N. L.), Is. of Wight Co;
S. side of Maherin River; on E. side
of the Great Sw., adj. his own land;
22 Feb. 1724, p. 221. 20 Shill,

EDWARD COLWELL, 375 acs. (N.
L.), Pr. Geo, Co; on both sides of the
Old Road, adj. Peter Jones, Junr; beg.
at. his Ist corner from the Great Cr;
to Wall's Run; & to Capt. Jones’ line;
17 Aug. 1725, p. 279. 40 Shill.

ROGER POWEL, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on N. side of James River;
adj.eJohn Pleasants’ land on Wolf ‘Br;
Ralph WHudspith’s line; & Benjamin
Johnson’s corner; 17 Aug, 1725, p.
284. 40 Shill.

WILLIAM FARLOWE, 137 acs, (N.
L.), Henrico Co; on S. side of James
River; adj. Martha Blankinship; Charles
Clay; John Farlowe; & Henry Walthall;
on N. side of a br. of Proctor’s (Cr.);
17 Aug. 1725, p. 287. 15 Shill.

WILLIAM BARNET, 341 acs. (N.
L.), Henrico Co; N. side of James -Riv;
adj. John Bradley; & Mr. John Woodson; & on N, side a br. of Allen’s Cr;
17 Aug. 1725, p. 305. 35 Shill.

ANN PRIDE, JANE PRIDE &
MARY PRIDE, 391 acs. (N. L.), Henrico Co; N. side of Appamatock Riv;
& on E, side of a br. of Butterwood Cr;
17 Aug. 1725, p. 307. 40 Shill.

JOHN FARMER, 400 acs., (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S$, side of James Riv;
17 Aug. 1725, p. 309. 40 Shill.

WILLIAM DUNIFUNT, 85 acs. (N,
L.), Henrico Co; on N. side of Appamatock Riv; adj. Mr. William Traylor;
Mr. George Archer; Mr. Mark Moore;
John Pattison, & Hugh Bragg; 17 Aug.
1725, p. 312. 10 Shill,

JOHN WOODRAM, 400 acs. (N.
L.), Henrico Co: on N. side of James
River; adj. John Gun; John Woodall;
Nowell Burton & Benjamin Woodson;
cn Joseph Woodson’s line, &c; 18 Mar.
1725, p. 344. 40 Shill.

JOHN SANDERS, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S. side of James River;
beg. on Stovall’s branch; on Bartholomew Stovall’s line; to Stovall's Creek;
24 Mar. 1725, p, 404. 40 Shill,

EDWARD HATCHER, 200 acs. (N.
L.), Henrico Co; adj. John Ellis’ land;
24 Mar. 1725, p. 407. 20 Shill.

CHARLES JUDKINS, 375. acs. (N.
L.), Surry Co; S. side of Nottoway
Riv., & on N. side of the Spring Sw;
adi. Henry Brown; & Jones Stokes’ line;
24 Mar, 1725, p. 431. 40 Shill.

JOHN LIGHTFOOT, 400 acs. (N.
L.}, Spotsyl. Co.; in St. George’s Par;
in the fork of Rappa, River; on Cedar
Run, cor, of Col. Alexander Spotswood ;
30 June 1726, p. 487.
400 acs. (N.
George’s Par:
corner of
side the Northanna;
june 1726, p. 487.

ROBERT SLAUGHTER, of Essex
Co; 214 acs. (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co;
above the Mountain Run, between lands
of Baylor & Taylor, & the Taliaferros’;
adj. Taliaferro in his brothers line, &c;
30 June .1726, p. 491.

WILLIAM EDINGS, 531 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
on E. side of the Mountain Run; adj.
William Connicoe’s line; Sharp's cor;
Capt. Lawrence (Taliaferro) & Capt.
John Taliaferro; 30 June 1726, p. 492.

CHARLES KEMBALL, of Surry Co;
280 acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co; on
low, side of the Reedy Cr. of Maherin
River; beg. below the Bever Pond, about
1144 mi. above the Governor's Roade;
on Sissom’s path; 7 July 1726, p. 506.

PETER MICHEL, SENR., of Pr. Geo.
Co; 238-acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co;
on S. side of Nottoway Riv., opposite
to his son Peter Michel's plantation;
delow mouth of Turkey Gutt; 7 July
1726, p. 507.

GEORGE WALTON, of Surry Co;
190 acs. (N. L.}, Brunswick Co; on S.
side of Maherin River; adj. Joha Wall;
7 July 1726, p. 312.

RALPH JACKSON, of Surry Co;
100 acs, (N. L.), Brunswick Co; S.
side of Maherin Riv; on Turkey Island;
7 July 1726, p, 518.

ROGER TILLMAN, of Pr. Geo. Co;
308 acs, (N. L.), Brunswick Co; in the
fork of Stoney Hill Run, on S, side of
Nottoway River; at a Licking Place;
7 July 1726, p. 532.
